24/03/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Police in Athens defused a bomb Wednesday (March 23rd) outside a tax office after a caller phoned in a warning to the local newspaper Eleftherotypia.
The tax office in the central Neos Kosmos district was evacuated immediately after the warning.
Nobody was hurt, nor has any group claimed responsibility yet.
(To Vima, Flashnews, Ta Nea - 23/03/11)
